entry.title: Feingold, McCain, Ryan Introduce Line-item Veto to Curb Wasteful Spending
entry.content: US Senator Russ Feingold (D-WI) and Senator John McCain (R-AZ), and Congressman Paul Ryan (R-WI) are reintroducing legislation to create a line-item veto to target wasteful earmarks, improve congressional accountability, and deter lawmakers from inserting Bridges to Nowhere or other frivolous spending into future bills. The legislation would enable the president to single out egregious earmarks in bills that arrive on his desk for signature and send these specific items back to Congress for ...

entry.title: Feingold on Progressive Change in the Senate
entry.content: Following in the tradition of Wisconsin progressivism, US Senator Russ Feingold is beginning this Congress with a focus on supporting working families, strengthening the voice of the people in government, protecting taxpayer dollars and restoring the rule of law. You can learn more about Senator Feingold at http://feingold.senate.gov.

entry.title: Feingold Introduces Bill to Spur Oil Production
entry.content: US Senator Russ Feingold speaks from the Senate floor on the introduction of the "use it or lose it" bill to spur oil production. July 10, 2008. The legislation, entitled the Responsible Federal Oil and Gas Lease Act, would spur oil companies to develop the 66 million acres of federal land they currently lease but have not developed to produce oil. More information is available at http://feingold.senate.gov/~feingold/releases/08/07/20080710.html
